<title>GERMANY: BASF says keeping up cost-cutting efforts.</title>
<headline>BASF says keeping up cost-cutting efforts.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1996-11-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>BASF AG chief financial officer Max Dietrich Kley said on Wednesday that the German chemicals group was keeping up its efforts to cut costs as well as jobs in Germany.</p>
<p>&quot;The cost cutting is an ongoing process all over the world,&quot; Kley told Reuters Financial Television in an interview.</p>
<p>&quot;I am sure that we have to reduce the headcount in Germany and we are working very hard on the environmental costs,&quot; he said. &quot;We will also bring down our energy costs to internationally-accessible levels.&quot;</p>
<p>Kley said BASF was in the process of moving some of its production and investment activities to the Asia-Pacific, including plans for China and later for Malaysia.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
